    "attributes": {
        "action": "Provide specific funding for Pain Infusion Therapy (PIT) on NHS",
        "additional_details": "This has been the ONLY treatment that has given me a substantial improvement in my quality of life, without it I am in constant pain, my pain consultant has no alternative to offer, the other medications available cause side effects and make life miserable, I have to wait until the 6th november to see my consultant, who has already informed me he has nothing to offer!",
        "background": "Lidocane ifusions as a treatment for Pain have been withdrawn as it has said there is insufficant benifit to justify its use, IF it dosnt work well for some people, then do not give it to them, just like any other treatment, do NOT remove it completely from all the people it does help,",
